  "texts": [
    "While VAE suffers from blurry results.",
    "As an alternative, diffusion models, which were first proposed in Sohl-Dickstein et al. [148], have recently come back into interest due to their training stability and their encouraging sample quality results for the creation of images and audio.",
    "As a result, as compared to other types of deep generative models, they may present more advantageous trade-offs.",
    "Diffusion models corrupt training data by gradually introducing Gaussian noise, gradually removing details until the data is pure noise, and then training a neural network to reverse this corruption.",
    "Running this reversed corruption procedure produces a clean sample by gradually denoising pure noise to create data from it."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "As an alternative, diffusion models, which were first proposed in Sohl-Dickstein et al. [148], have recently come back into interest due to their training stability and their encouraging sample quality results for the creation of images and audio."
